quotes.!chatgpt: Programs such as ChatGPT are language processors and not true AI; they will confidently spew nonsense that only a true expert can tell from fiction, thus they are strongly discouraged when you are trying to learn a new technical skill such as coding or mod-making as they can make it harder to learn how to do things correctly.
quotes.!sequence: Try to avoid using `PatchOperationSequence` because it can obfuscate errors and make it difficult to figure out what's wrong. You only need it if you are sequencing multiple patches off of a PatchOperationFindMod or PatchOperationConditional, and in the former case if you have enough patches you should consider using LoadFolders.xml instead. Please see https://rimworldwiki.com/wiki/Modding_Tutorials/PatchOperations for more information.
